Great article by the NY Times about how communities organize themselves when no one seems to care about them. I expect to see more and more of these local networks over time. This quote stood out for me :
Joshua Breitbart, a senior fellow at New America Foundation&rsquo;s Open Technology Institute, which created the software that helps the Red Hook mesh operate, said digital culture was too focused on the global, as opposed to the local. &ldquo;The general narrative of Silicon Valley is, build an app and change the world,&rdquo; Mr. Breitbart said. &ldquo;There should be room to say, &lsquo;Build an app and change my neighborhood.&rsquo; &rdquo;
Is this the dawn of hyperlocal software development?
